The tenant of Bakal: The stoves are heated, he signed a higher rent.
An imposing elderly man came out of the door of the RPG Byty customer center of the "coal baron" Zdenek Bakal, the largest private owner of apartments for rent in the Czech Republic.
He was carrying under his arm a file with three new rental contracts for three apartments: his own, his daughter’s and his son’s who is pursuing a sentence.
The deregulation increased the rent to these three people.
Instead of paying 3500 the son will have to pay from next year for a 2+1 second category apartment 4100 crowns.
"And there is no hot water and the heating works with solid fuel," the man who has the signing power pointed to his son's new contract.
"But I signed anyway," he said in anger and half resigned.
The citizen association of apartments BytyOKD.cz, which described the new rental conditions as "immoral and indecent", advises tenants not to sign and wait until December 7, when a notice will be issued to explain the method to be followed to claim.
But the man reacts to it with a gesture of the hand.
"One says this, the other says something else" by frowning at the eyebrows.
The Ostrava region becomes the laboratory of deregulation.
After the New Year, this is what most apartments in the Czech Republic whose rents do not match the market price expect.
Aktualne.cz has therefore decided to personally visit the "laboratory".
The RPG waiting room in Havirovska Street is one of four in the Ostrava region and is already full on Tuesday at 9 a.m.
Right next to the door stands a security company guard with a device to call customers.
A special button, "rent 2011", is turned on on the touch screen.
A single press and a paper with a number comes out of the device.
You don't have time to read your number "157" as your number is already starting to illuminate on the big screen under the top of the waiting room.
In a fraction of a second, it's your turn.
After a short moment, an old couple arrives to inquire about the rent, but the new rents do not seem to concern people in the waiting room.
The majority of people have come to solve common problems as everywhere - requests for repairs, events related to insurance and others.
In the Ostrava region, people from more than 44,000 RPG portfolio apartments have been receiving mail with new leases in their mailbox since about mid-November.
RPG Byty offers them rent increases from 15 to 38 percent.
The special ticket office for new rentals has been open to the public since November 18.
"It's been working for almost a week, so it's still on trial," the employee answers, after a moment of hesitation, behind the counter when the client presents himself as a journalist.
The derailment and old miners' apartments in Bakal are a very sensitive local subject.
The Vice-President of the Parliament and native of the Ostrava region Lubomir Zaoralek of the Social Democrats stated this quite strongly before the elections and it now fills the local newspapers.
"Twenty years after them, I want a new floor."
"They didn't even change me a putt of a board in the toilet, the man mentioned in the introduction is relieved.
However, it is mostly, according to employees, retirees who come to be sure they will receive a discount on the new rental price if they sign now as promised RPG in a special offer.
This is a rebate of half the amount of the rent that will be received by the other tenants who have signed their new contract before December 15.
But the "deregulation" counter on Havirovaska Street is really not overwhelmed by questions.
“Of the 360 customers who came yesterday, only 40 to 50 came for rent,” she said.
And yet RPG puts both on its website and in the showcases of individual interviews on rents when necessary.
If both parties do not agree on the rent, it is an independent court that will make the decision.
“It’s not about threats, it’s just about informing about the unique and legitimate way to act legally,” RPG said in a statement.
"Here no one will go to court" thinks one of the employees of RPG Byty and the man in the street in front of the customer center gives her right.
“I have 13,000 crowns of retirement and I have 5,000 crowns left to eat, I don’t have enough to go to court,” he says.
The employee suddenly feels uncomfortable with it.
"We'll see."
"Mr. Zaoralek in the media asks that no one sign and so people wait," she said.
The regulation of rents ends in the Czech Republic with the beginning of 2011 and the increases, according to RPG Byty, are an economic necessity.
"And, moreover, current rents still do not reach the level necessary for the simple maintenance of the housing fund," recalls Pavel Klimes, director of the residential portfolio of the company RPG Byty, that it is precisely the neglect of the housing fund that makes the tenant angry is the main reason for the increase.
However, in 5 years between 2005 and 2010 RPG was able with rents to invest in apartments 4 billion, in four years from 2011 to 2014 that should be 5.2 billion.
The large screen hanging from the ceiling in front of the upholstered armchairs in the waiting room on Haverosvka Street, however, repeats some information indicated in red.
The rental increase in 2011 is 15 percent and affects no less than 31,200 apartments or more than 90 percent of RPG apartments.
"And it will always be at most 7.50 Czech crowns per m2 per month," the screen says.
The 38 percent increase concerns only 400 apartments in the RPG portfolio.
"In these cases, this is an increase of a really very low amount of 19.66 Czech crowns per m2", adds RPG.
Next year the rent will remain the same for 2,600 apartments.
RPG Byty promises that deregulation will not cause a radical but progressive increase over 4 to 8 years.
It adds other commitments: all the money from the increase in rents (see graph) is returned to the apartments in the form of heating savings - new windows and heating.
Those who sign the agreement on the increase in rent have priority.
The kindergarten is also part of the offices comprised of the architects.
the administrative building Avriopoint in Brno is the new headquarters of the company Arch. Design.
No one could have expected it to also house a mini kindergarten with everything you need - colored walls, imaginative furniture, toys and finally a miniature playground on the terrace.
Since October last year, the children of Arch. design employees can visit.
The architectural project company Arch. Design. whose workshops produced a large number of constructions in Brno, has imagined its mini kindergarten business since the first drafts of the Avriopoint building.
It employs about 90 people, especially those of childbearing age, and it was important for women architects and project managers to be able to return to work quickly.
Along with reduced-time employment contracts, the kindergarten is a bonus offered to its employees by the Arch. Design. company as part of its social program.
Builders and architects have the opportunity to combine work that takes care of children.
It was the employees of Arch.Design themselves who imagined this kindergarten and with the support of the management they were able to obtain an endowment from the European Union and the Ministry of Labour and Social Affairs.
The mini kindergarten is funded by the European Social Fund through the Human Resources Operational Programme and the State Budget of the Czech Republic.
Thanks to the funding (in the amount of CZK 2.8 million), they were able to purchase equipment and appliances and after two years ensure qualified personnel as well as the launch.
After using the funding endowment (two years) the company Arch. Design. has the obligation after 3 years to operate the mini kindergarten on its own funds.
The preparation of the project took a year and it was the company Economy rating that helped to make the application for the endowment.
Child care is provided by qualified staff, all day a nurse and a kindergarten teacher take care of the children. children can go to kindergarten without age limitation but they have more than three years for most.
As this is a "mini kindergarten" there can only be 5 children present at the same time, but during the day there are more who replace each other.
The operation of the school is flexible according to the needs of the parents and the children of all employees have the same right to use this school without regard to the hierarchical position.
Although it is an individual care and education, the program of the mini kindergarten is comparable to that for preschool education.
Children don't just play, but quality education is also ensured - from the beginning to preparation for school benches, English is taught.
The class is equipped not only with imaginative toys and games but also with a computer that children can use.
The presence of young children in society creates a friendly and positive environment.
Parents can at any time control their child and not have the stress of a delay to go to pick up the children in a school far from the parents' workplace.
Therefore, parents use their working time in the most productive way.
It is not surprising that a natural relationship of loyalty is created between the employee and the employer.
Arch.Design.s is thus listed among the companies that offer a bonus of choice for the recruitment of new employees and are friendly to the family and through this program strengthens the marketing of HR.
The house in bones still fascinates after 100 years. Take a look at Gaudi’s interiors.
The roof resembles the back of a prehistoric saurian, the staircase to a dinosaur spine, and the balconies to open fish mouths.
This is the Casa Battlo house in Barcelona by the architect Antoni Gaudi.
Due to its organic forms, the house has received from the locals the nickname of House in Bone.
Organic shapes, wild colors, unusual use of stones, fragments of tiles and mosaics, a facade reminiscent of scales and everywhere present curves, that is all that is ypic for Art Nouveau by Antoni Gaudi.
The front facade of the house unfolds its dream lines, its pleasant colors and textures that remind nature and animals.
In the course of a more detailed observation one can see the geometry, the rhythm and the order thought with precision.
At night the facade of the house becomes even more dramatic and is lit in such a way that the impression of brightness of colors is reinforced.
The winding and twisting of the shapes also appears in the interiors with the same measure.
Wood waves copy window frames, balustrades, decorative elements of doors, eyelets and slats.
The Battlo house, which stands in the Eixample district in the shopping street Passeig de Gracia at number 43, was born from the construction of an 1877 house by the architect Emilio Sala Cortes.
The reconstruction took two years and the house was completed in 1906.
The investor, Joseph Battlo, a wealthy entrepreneur, first insisted on the demolition of the old building and the construction of an entirely new one, but quickly accepted Gaudi's idea of an unusual and cheaper reconstruction.
But the idea of Casa Battlo as a multi-apartment house was not thought of by Gaudi alone.
The architect Josep Maria Jujol worked with him.
It is precisely on his project that the decorations for a representative apartment of the owner of the building and the use of the mosaic for the facade were born.
For the facade also worked other artists and creators.
The joint work for the Casa Battlo plans began with a successful cooperation between Jujol and Gaudi.
Jujol participated in the construction of Gaudi's Casa Mila and the Park Güell in which there are other works of Gaudi.
The locals nicknamed the hot house just after its finish because of its organic shapes "the House in Bone".
Others, given the specific mechanism of opening the windows, called it "the house that barks".
It is said that at the top of the construction there is a sword similar to that of Saint George the patron of Catalonia.
Other elements of the construction sculpture contain hidden religious motifs.
Gaudi thought for the house a unique system in its central heating time,with ventilation fans and typical fireplaces.
Their 45-degree tilt seems strange.
During the creation Gaudi absolutely did not comply with the construction guidelines of the time and did not allow himself to be hindered by them.
At the beginning of the construction he obtained from the city the permission to build, knowing, of course, that the data on the reconstruction plans were so vague that two years later during the completion the municipal council was horrified and asked for changes.
For example, the members of the municipal council did not like the pillars of construction being embedded on the public sidewalk.
There was never any modification, but, on the contrary, only 15 days after the call from the city Josep Battlo requested (and obtained satisfaction) permission to rent the two highest floors.
The owner moved to the lower floors.
In the gallery on the second floor there was a common living room and in the third one a bedroom and a private part of the apartment.
The ground floor was rented to a jewelry store.
The entire six-storey house is shared by a staircase that leads to an independent roof terrace.
All right angles and straight lines were cancelled by the basic elements of the reconstruction and replaced with curved walls.
Gaudi also worked on the modern concept of connecting spaces.
The common part can be completely connected by opening the doors of the lounges and the high society can communicate comfortably or limit private space for more intimate interviews.
The house with the reconstruction of Gaudi received in addition to new facades a non-traditional roof and two additional floors.
Gaudi’s play with the light is also impressive, blue and white glazed tiles with which the courtyard is decorated and with wells of lights.
The two-color set gives maximum light in all floors of the house.
It was enough to simply bet on the principle that white reflects more than dark which, on the contrary, absorbs the rays of the sun.
The Casa Battlo house that was inscribed in 2005 in the UNESCO World Heritage Fund may be visited by everyone.
On the first floor of the house is the most spacious and splendid apartment accessible to the public.
The owners decided to take this step in 2002 on the occasion of the 150th anniversary of the birth of the famous creator.
They continued the visits because they found it to be a lucrative business and they expanded the scope of visits to common areas and attic including roof terraces.
The entrance ticket to the monument is really cheap and costs 16.50 euros; students, retirees, groups and tourist card holders have 20 percent discount.
The sum is still above the entry price in Gaudi's other buildings in the city.
If you want to feel the real atmosphere of the house with its fantastic turrets, you need to quickly find a comrade among the inhabitants of the building and visit the house completely.
How to choose a mattress and a mattress: women have different criteria than men.
No ostentatious frame, but rather the quality of the surface reserved for the bed, so the mattress and sommier give a real basis for a good bed.
They must of course complement each other harmoniously to please a concrete user.
During the selection several things are decisive:the weight, height, age, health status as well as the sex of the owner.
The type of interior in which the mattress and sommier will be placed is also important.
A typical example?
For example, in the country house where you do not sleep continuously latex mattresses are not suitable because they "warm up" gently.
They also have a higher weight than standard polyurethane mattresses.
It is necessary to return them frequently.
If they also do not have enough ventilation channels at the heart and if they remain, in addition, on a solid board, they retain moisture. Mold can also form there.
Habit is also crucial in the choice.
One who spends the clear of time abroad where very thick mattresses are frequently used with a softening layer, will hardly feel good on a low and hard surface.
"That's how all hockey players who come back from the NHL complain that they can't sleep there."
"For their tired shoulders, feet and ribs, they needed mattresses with a softening layer of lazy foam."
"Such mattresses are also recommended for people who suffer from diabetes who have a nervous system disorder that therefore misappropriate the "information" of the joints and skin," explains Sylva Adamczikova, who specializes in upholstered furniture.
This is why a few years ago the mattress with lazy foam conquered hockey players as well as other customers.
"Today everything is going well, Tempur, the Italian Magnifex but also the Czech Tropico for example have suitable mattresses.
You don't have to be an NHL guy to enjoy a lazy foam.
This “miracle” simply works.
It optimizes its rigidity and shape depending on the heat absorbed or adapts to the heat of your body.
Nothing puts pressure on you and you won’t turn around at night like you did after a tough match.
You just sleep better.
The lazy foam also acts as a protection against squalls.
To choose the mattress according to your size, add the length of the feet, which is about 21/34 cm.
A man and a woman with a size of 180cm therefore need a bed of 210/220cm.
The minimum width for each for a two-seater bed should be 90 cm or 180 cm in total.
For single beds, for example singles, it is recommended to take at least 120 /140 cm.
It is convenient in case of a visit.
"However, there is a simple rule for the width of the bed: when you are lying on the back you should lay your hands comfortably with the elbows slightly folded. Helena Prokopova, President of the Association of Materiel-Mathematicians and Decorators who has dedicated for several years to the problem of mobilizing and sleeping in the school.
For a two-seater bed each needs its own bunk and mattress, so be careful however during the purchase to choose the height of the mattress.
Otherwise you will only have to mount the sofa at different heights and this is not feasible on all bed frames.
Foam mattresses should have a minimum height of 14 cm, spring mattresses at least 15 cm, of this count for the layer of form and ventilation at least three centimeters.
"When touching or sitting on the mattress you should not feel the springs," warns Helena Prokopova.
Each mattress requires a well-defined type of sommer.
The bunk bed, when the mattress and the bunk bed are united like Siamese sisters, has nothing to do in the bedrooms.
The mattresses went very badly; it should not be washed, which is commonly done today.
And since during the night sweats normally from 0.2 to 0.75 l of sweat, it is clear that after 5/7 years, the mattress begins to resemble a large (and stuffed) sieve.
For this reason, the specialists refuse to make a claim over a lifespan of 25 years for a mattress or a lifetime warranty.
But everything at home.
And for this an experience advice from the sellers: for a mattress of 120/140cm, give up, for the covering of the mattress, hygiene or washing but instead add a protective mattress that you can easily remove and wash.
And even if nowadays it is common to make zippered coatings for the whole set, that is to say that after opening you have two parts (for washing and the size of the washing machine it is very important!) otherwise the manipulation for the large models (and for one person) becomes a problem when you remove the ring between them.
Do you have a rigid board in your bed instead of a sommier?
Never! Never!
Maximum for a bed for visitors for one night only.
However, equip the board (if there are none) with aeration holes and use the spring mattress with a minimum height of 15cm with pocket springs (from Germany Taschenfederken) and a layer of aeration.
A polyurethane mattress should not be part of such a bed.
For single-position slatted mattresses with 14/18 slats, the latex mattresses or so-called sandwiches (maybe the combination of latex and coconut), are ideal but it will always be better for you to have a mattress with more slats, 28 and above, where the slats are doubled from the lower part of the back.
For multi-position mattresses do not take spring mattresses as it does not respond to position changes.
In addition to adjusting the rigidity of the slats, a so-called shoulder cradle can also be installed.
This is a special connection of the slats that allows the slat to be pressed or even tilted so that the shoulder of the sleeping person "integrates" well.
For men who have “shoulders as wide as their backs,” it’s really important.
This is already considered by the mattress manufacturers who for the "masculine" have begun to use a softening area at the level of the shoulders.
But they also think of women - they offer them a softer surface at the hips again.
For the most difficult customer there are wing or plate tops with what is called a multiforce suspension.
The pressure spreads in more points and decreases the tension.
But of course, be careful, as soon as you use a bad pillow (large and puffy air) on good mattresses and soother, the "plus" disappears.
The basic rule is a simple pillow: the pillow should support the head and its tips should reach only the shoulders, so that the shoulder muscles can rest.
The recommended size is 50X60 cm which Scandinavians for example prefer.
When lying on the side, the pillow should level the height of the shoulders (with the shoulder cradle of the sommer or the area soaked in the mattress).
Modern mattresses still have something in common with the first ones based on straw and herbs.
Manufacturers still use natural materials or mixtures.
The trend is also in the organic mattress.
Petroleum-based raw materials, from which polyurethane is made, are replaced by natural oils, such as soybean oil.
Almost all known manufacturers use precisely soybeans.
“The Bio label for mattresses means that the heart is made from natural products,” says Petr Vasicek of Tropico Plus.
Natural materials are also used for mattress linings; one of the first was aloe vera.
But you can add micro-capsules that develop scents of forest or lavender.
There are differences between man and woman.
While birch plant extract so that the mattress lining absorbs heat and cools the body, "cools" the man, the linings "warm" women.
Red pepper extract accelerates blood circulation and is therefore hotter for weak sex.
The current favorites?
The mattresses made from cold foam (it has more pores with a disturbed cellular structure therefore more breathable than standard polyurethane and has more elasticity.
The combination of different rigidities of cold foams gives polyzone mattresses that know exactly where the head, lower back and feet are located.
You will pay a quality mattress from 7000 crowns and more.
Those that are characterized by their health parameters have less VAT and are taken as instruments for health.
In the Czech Republic, Gumotex reached the first place.
Saving for the mattress and sommier is not easy.
From time to time, two mattresses may be available for the price of one as part of special promotions by manufacturers or producers.
For example the company Magniflex that offers Duofreeze mattresses with Memory foam sewn to the lining for 11990 crowns.
The second one can be taken for free.
The era of lazy or viscoelastic foams with an open cellular structure and a large thickness was started with Tempur matter at a "cosmic" rate.
This began as a matter for NASA because astronauts were undergoing huge loading factors at the start.
Tempur softens in the heat and hardens, on the contrary, in the cold.
It therefore adapts perfectly to the warm human body and distributes it an optimal pressure.
It is ideal for this against poor sleep and for increased comfort during sleep.
Viscoelastic foams are used not only for mattresses but also for health products, such as special foot cushions that relieve the legs and the venous system.
Czech manufacturers use, for example, EucathermC or Twinsaver foam or the same type.
Devices to track people are increasingly in demand by parents who want to monitor their children.
Fear for their child leads more and more people to think about monitoring them through a GPS.
The system, set up at the beginning to search for cars, can also be used to trace the movement of people and help in some cases, such as that of little Anicka Janatkova.
The instrument is currently as large as a lighter box but will soon be the size of a watch.
The case of little Anicka touched a lot of people and they started looking for ways to better protect their children.
Even if the price is to disturb their privacy.
“We are trying to tell everyone that this is not espionage but just another way to reduce the likelihood of another tragedy,” says Petr Pilin of MAcro Weil, one of the leading tracking devices suppliers in the Czech market.
"I admit that there may be cases of misuse of such devices, such as putting it in the bag of a person who is not aware, but I have not yet encountered such cases."
“The majority of people are customers who actually buy the product for safety reasons,” adds Pilin.
According to him, children should always know for what purposes the "box" is used and how to use it in an emergency.
Child psychologist, Dana Bockova, draws attention to the fact that if the child does not want to wear such a thing on him, he will get rid of it.
“Even the little ones can show great creativity when it comes to deliberately getting rid of something when they don’t want to be under control.”
“Mobile phones, which can cut like these tracking devices, have already led parents to long expectations,” says Bockova.
According to her, the fact that this type of device can help in case of aggression is highly questionable.
“If it’s a prepared kidnapping, the author will do everything to ensure that the child doesn’t have an electronic device that can locate him.”
“Actually, it’s the phone.”
“As soon as the tracking devices are going to develop, they (the criminals) are going to pick them up, too, because the sale will be supported by an advertising campaign.”
"In such cases, the criminals will always be ahead of the police," says the psychologist.
She admits, however, that such devices can help during an unprepared aggression by a pedophile.
According to Robert Cech of RC Monitoring, which offers tracking services for both cars and people, having this type of device can help, even if it is destroyed in the event of an assault.
"The device may be configured in such a way that it is in regular transmission after a certain period of time."
"In the event that the device is destroyed, it still remains the last position of the person concerned."
"The more expensive devices also have an inclinometer that immediately signals the position of the person who slipped and finds himself in a lying position without moving," Cech said.
According to him, so-called smart phones that are equipped with a navigation system, can offer a comparable service after having formatted it with a special prologue.
The problem with the current tracking systems is that it is either a device similar to those that are worn as a pendant of the size of a lighter box or to the smallest telephone devices.
We can always lose them.
According to Pilina of Macro Weil, this is why tests are currently being conducted to make devices that look like common digital watches.
"This will have the advantage that the potential attacker will not be able to recognize the tracking device."
"Or he will realize it after a while, which will give the police a little more time," he added.
Whether the tracing device is developed in the form of a bracelet or a pendant, it will always use the same technology as for tracing cars.
This is a combination of position acquisition systems using GPS (which is commonly used in self-navigation) and a mobile phone function that alerts the current position of a vehicle.
