A city has demanded that all new recruits have a postgraduate degree.
The province of Guangdong has exchanged gray-green uniforms for a more engaging blue.
Wuhan, in central China, replaced the low-eyed with the strong way: In 2009, a report reported that 50 officers had surrounded an uncontrollable snack cart by casting black glances, firmly for half an hour, until the colporteur packed his belongings and left.
Xindu, an urban district of 680,000 inhabitants in Chengdu, chose to do a major image operation.
Since 2003, the district has supplemented its urban street police with 13 women, specially chosen for their appearance, elbow and young age.
